cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language modeling and part-of-speech tagging. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper introduces a new model for constructing vector representations of words. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses bidirectional LSTMs for composing characters. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with vector representations and neural networks, which are also used in computer vision.
